&lt;Kaiser Steel Corp>'s plant inNapa, Calif., has been purchased by Oregon Steel Mills for 16mln dlrs, the privately owned Portland company said.    The transaction was approved by the U.S. bankruptcy judgein Denver who is hearing Kaiser Steel's Chapter 11reorganization case.    James Mccaughey, former vice president of sales for Kaiser,has been named general manager for the plant which will becalled Napa Pipe Corp, Oregon Steel said. Reuter&#3;